snippet.textDisplay: There are thousands of similar well-meaning comments across Coke studio songs.  Let's just say this.  Indians love our music, we love their movies.  The people don't have an issue as we get along when we're not inundated with propaganda.  But let's both be clear about one thing.  India is a country and Pakistan is a country.  Let's respect that.  Pakistanis find it deeply offensive to be suggested the idea of "one country, one people". Our roots are obviously similar but just as India was created in 1947 (there was no country called India before that, just princely states) so was Pakistan.  Love is one thing, geography and political identity is another.  Let's not confuse the two nor keep the two conditional on the other.
snippet.textOriginal: There are thousands of similar well-meaning comments across Coke studio songs.  Let's just say this.  Indians love our music, we love their movies.  The people don't have an issue as we get along when we're not inundated with propaganda.  But let's both be clear about one thing.  India is a country and Pakistan is a country.  Let's respect that.  Pakistanis find it deeply offensive to be suggested the idea of "one country, one people". snippet.textDisplay:
TRANSLATION | SUBTITLE

Ae Rah-e-Haq Ke Shaheedo =  O, the Martyrs of the Right Path
Wafa ki taswero = Depiction of faithfulness
Tumhe watan ki hawayen salam kehti hain = Breeze of this country salutes you
Ae Rah-e-Haq Ke Shaheedo =  O, the Martyrs of the Right Path

ALLAH HOOO

Lagane Aag Jo Aye The Ashyane Ko  = Those who came to burn aerie
Woh Sholey Apne Lahoo Se Bujhadiye Tumnee  = You put off those flames with your blood.
Bachalaiya Hai yateemi se Kitne Pholon Ko = You saved so many flowers (kids) from orphanhood 
Suhag Kitni Baharon K Rakh Liye Tumnee = You saved so many springs (married females) from being widowed
Tumhe Chaman Ki Fazain Salam Kheti Hain  = Skies of this garden salutes you 
Ae Rah-e-Haq Ke Shaheedo =  O, the Martyrs of the Right Path

Chale Jo Hoge Shahadat Ka Jaam Piker Tum = You went away after tasting martyrdom
Rasool-e-pak Ne Banhoon Main Leliya Hoga  = Prophet (P.B.U.H) must have embraced you in his arms.
Ali Tumhari Shuja\'at Pay Jhomte Honge  = Ali (A.S) must be proud of you bravery
Husain Pak Ne Irshad Yeh Kya Hoga = Hussain (A.S) must have said
Tumnhe Khuda Ki Razain Salam Kehti Hain = Lord's pleasures salute you
Ae Rah-e-Haq Ke Shaheedo =  O, the Martyrs of the Right Path
